text.tspan: Road vehicles per 1000 inhabitants vs GDP per capita, 2014
Road motor vehicle ownership measured per 1000 inhabitants versus gross domestic product (GDP) per capita,
measured in 2011 international-$. 'Motor vehicle' includes automobiles, SUVs, trucks, vans, buses, commercial
vehicles and freight motor road vehicles. This data excludes motorcycles and other two-wheelers.
Source: NationMaster Database; World Bank - World Development Indicators (WDI)
